Today, I took to the House floor to honor the life and service of SGT Michael Verardo. 

He was a true American hero who dedicated his life to helping fellow wounded warriors through tireless advocacy. He leaves behind a remarkable legacy and a beautiful family who loved him dearly.

I went on CBS News to make one thing clear:  Republicans are getting things done — from cutting taxes for working families to making sure the government is funded responsibly. Reckless Dems want a shutdown instead of working with the majority because they don’t like President Trump. That’s not how governing works.

Today, we laid to rest American hero SGT Michael Verardo — a husband, father, and patriot who gave everything for this country.

After being severely injured by IED attacks in Afghanistan, he came home and continued the fight on behalf of wounded veterans. I was honored to know Michael and his wife, Sarah, through their advocacy work that improved outcomes and changed the lives of countless veterans, including legislation we passed at the North Carolina General Assembly. 

Michael inspired so many Americans with his bravery, his resiliency, and his love for his fellow service members and our nation. We owe Michael and his family a debt of gratitude we cannot repay, but I ask you to pray for Sarah, his daughters, and the rest of his family as they navigate this heartbreaking loss and continue the mission Michael relentlessly championed.

Today, we thank and celebrate the hardworking Americans who strengthen our communities and move our nation forward.
